<p>Weather is one of the first things people talk about in any language. In Chinese, it's the go-to small talk topic — at the bus stop, in the elevator, with your neighbor, or when starting a phone call with family. Mastering weather vocabulary opens the door to effortless daily conversation.</p>

<p>This guide covers <strong>70+ weather-related words</strong>, from basic conditions like sunny and rainy to temperature expressions, seasonal vocabulary, severe weather terms, and the cultural idioms that Chinese speakers use every day. Whether you're planning a trip to China or Taiwan, preparing for the <a href="/chinese/blog/hsk-preparation/">HSK exam</a>, or just want to chat naturally, this vocabulary will keep the conversation flowing.</p>

